1. What are we doing today?  
Weâ€™ll learn how to handle both JSON and XML responses from APIs. Many APIs return either of these formats, and we need to validate them properly.

ðŸ’¡ Example: JSON is like a list of items in a grocery cart, while XML is more structured with tags, like labels on each item.

---

2. Code for Implementation

java
public class Json_Xml {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        baseURI = "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com";
        // Handling JSON Response
        given()
                .when()
                .get("/posts/1")
                .then()
                .statusCode(200)
                .body("userId", equalTo(1))
                .body("title", equalTo("sunt aut facere repellat provident occaecati excepturi optio reprehenderit"));

// Handling XML Response
        given()
                .when()
                .get("/users/1")
                .then()
                .statusCode(200)
                .body("name", equalTo("Leanne Graham"));

    }
}



---

3. Practice Questions  
1. Write tests to validate both JSON and XML responses for the same endpoint.  
2. Validate that specific fields exist in both response formats.  
3. Handle nested JSON and XML elements to extract values.

